postcontent:
Up for sale is a very gently used Smith & Wesson M&P15T. Bought this new in 2008; Has had less than 250 rounds through it. 

This is the premium tactical version that they made for the first couple years of production ( purchased this one in 2008 – it retailed then for $1,770 ). 

This model has the Troy folding battle sights and aluminum quad rail. Also has chrome lined barrel. 

In 2011 S&W cheaped it out and started using cheaper sights and poly rails on this gun as well as did away with the quality barrel; current models are just under $1,200.

Comes with the original S&W hard case, paperwork, manual, S&W rubber forearm covers, 30 round mag, etc. 

This one came with a full, four rail picatinny rail style front forearm and full picatinny rail flat top (as pictured front rails have rubberized S&W grip covers).

It is full parkerized finish with a  16” chrome lined barrel, 1:9 twist in .223/5.56.
Came factory with a six position telescoping stock and flip up troy battle sites.
It has Warne high rise quick detach, back to zero scope mounts and a BSA Sweet 223 scope with original box & paperwork (scope has built in bullet compensation adjustments and multiple turrets for different grained bullets – I believe it is a 3-12 x 40) and Butler Creek flip up scope caps. Pictured also with a front post grip. The grip has a compartment in the handle accessible under the cap on the bottom of it to store extra batteries or whatever. The light is an O-Light M20 Warrior tactical light. I believe it is 275 lumens with the strobe feature and a button specifically for the strobe. The light has a pressure switch (on the right side of the post grip), rail mount and extra reflector and original case and paperwork/manual. 

In addition, I have four extra 20 round magazines, two additional 30 round magazines (all A.R. Stoner mag.s), two magazine couplers and 600+ rounds of factory new ammo; most is 55 grain FMJ copper, (540 rounds new in box, 40 rounds of factory new in box steel, 20 tracers and somewhere around 100 loose rounds between the loaded mag.s and blue box pictured). I also have a soft case I could throw in (not pictured) for bargaining if required.

Please be advised... this is also for sale in other areas and what is pictured may be sold off individually.

title: For Trade:  PIF for someone truly in need!!
postcontent:
ay it forward to someone truly in need.

For anyone who lives by or has gone down by the Renton Landing area you might have seen this man. He is a older weathered looking homeless man. Most times you see him he is wearing the same older sweat shirt with a string tied around his waist to keep it together, and some old dirtied pants. However every time you see him he will be walking around with several old plastic bags in which he keeps all his valuables so they don't become ruined by the elements. My wife and I have seen him in the Landing area walking around minding his own business not bothering anyone. As far as we have seen he normally spends most nights out in the semi wooded area behind Lowell's. There have been times where we have driven by and seen him hunkered down with bags all around him to "try" and keep himself dry in the rain. 

We also normally will see him in the Target down there shopping, the Target management is nice enough to supply him with a gift card so he is able to buy somethings for himself however they all seem to be of course the biggest bang for his meager buck. Each time I've either driven by him or the wife and I have seen him in Target looking around making small talk with whomever will give him more than a smile and move on. Each time we both think we need to do something for him, I should help him in someway. Tonight we both realized that we had to do something for this sad polite human being. The wife first stopped to look at some beauty products when we noticed him looking at a mirror and put it back. I thought nothing really I saw him and then looked back at my phone to see what was new on SGN. However my wife is much smarter than me. She realized that what he was doing was looking at himself in the mirror.. Looking at himself. Something so small we take it for granted.

We both turned to each other and reached into our pocket and pulled what small amount of cash we had out. When we was kinda by himself I approached him. I didn't want to embarrass him, or make him think he was just getting a hand out. I quietly went up and said "Sir my wife and I would like you to have this." Shook his hand and gave him the cash. Now we could just pat ourselves on our backs and move on until next time we see him. However I have to do more, if I don't my inner boyscout would be ashamed. I would like to have just done this myself but being unemployed with zero income besides my amazing wifes I can't.

NOW THE IMPORTANT STUFF...
Thank you for making it through the back story, sorry I'm not as talent of a writer as I would like to be. What I am asking for is any of your old SHTF items. I'm looking for bags, backpacks, cold weather gear, hygiene gear, waterproof gear, socks, knives,one man tents, sleeping bags, bevy sacks. Anything that could improve someones live in these extremely cold and wet nights and days.

I'm starting this off with a...
Gortex USMC poncho, some cold weather items, and some hygiene gear and whatever else I have that I haven't gone through yet.
